"{\"uid\": \"themoscowtimes.com-2024-09-25-muzzled-in-the-west-rt-still-reaches-audiences-across-the-globe-a86454\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"\\\"They close entry to us, and we will go through the window.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 59, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"entry\", \"from\": 12, \"to\": 17}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 21, \"to\": 23}, {\"ngram\": \"the window\", \"from\": 48, \"to\": 58}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Close the window and we will go through the vents.\\\"\", \"from\": 60, \"to\": 111, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the window\", \"from\": 66, \"to\": 76}, {\"ngram\": \"the vents\", \"from\": 100, \"to\": 109}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thus spoke Margarita Simonyan, editor-in-chief of RT, anticipating the inevitable sanctions issued last week when the U.S. accused the outlet of being part of a Kremlin-backed campaign to influence November's presidential election.\", \"from\": 113, \"to\": 344, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 124, \"end\": 142, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Margarita_Simonyan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Margarita Simonyan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Margarita_Simonyan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Margarita_Simonyan\"}, {\"begin\": 163, \"end\": 165, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RT_America\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.022948913856875e-36, \"text\": \"RT\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RT_America\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RT_America\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"editor\", \"from\": 144, \"to\": 150}, {\"ngram\": \"chief\", \"from\": 154, \"to\": 159}, {\"ngram\": \"the inevitable sanctions\", \"from\": 180, \"to\": 204}, {\"ngram\": \"the U.S.\", \"from\": 227, \"to\": 235}, {\"ngram\": \"the outlet\", \"from\": 244, \"to\": 254}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 264, \"to\": 268}, {\"ngram\": \"a Kremlin-backed campaign\", \"from\": 272, \"to\": 297}, {\"ngram\": \"November's presidential election\", \"from\": 311, \"to\": 343}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Simonyan's personal social media, as well as the accounts linked to RT and Rossiya Segodnya, have also been blocked on Facebook and Instagram.\", \"from\": 345, \"to\": 487, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 413, \"end\": 415, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RT_America\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.022948913856875e-36, \"text\": \"RT\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RT_America\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RT_America\"}, {\"begin\": 420, \"end\": 436, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rossiya_Segodnya\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rossiya Segodnya\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rossiya_Segodnya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rossiya_Segodnya\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Simonyan's personal social media\", \"from\": 345, \"to\": 377}, {\"ngram\": \"the accounts\", \"from\": 390, \"to\": 402}, {\"ngram\": \"Facebook\", \"from\": 464, \"to\": 472}, {\"ngram\": \"Instagram\", \"from\": 477, \"to\": 486}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But while the U.S. seals the cracks in the windows to keep out Russian state-funded broadcasting, the door remains wide open across Africa, Latin America and the Middle East.\", \"from\": 489, \"to\": 663, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 552, \"end\": 559, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language\", \"score\": 0.9935948759219542, \"rank\": 0.006446412902383996, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the U.S.\", \"from\": 499, \"to\": 507}, {\"ngram\": \"the cracks\", \"from\": 514, \"to\": 524}, {\"ngram\": \"the windows\", \"from\": 528, \"to\": 539}, {\"ngram\": \"the door\", \"from\": 587, \"to\": 595}, {\"ngram\": \"Africa\", \"from\": 621, \"to\": 627}, {\"ngram\": \"Latin America\", \"from\": 629, \"to\": 642}, {\"ngram\": \"the Middle East\", \"from\": 647, \"to\": 662}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Figures regarding audience size are difficult to find and far from reliable, not least because RT's content is frequently spread across social media - often un-attributed.\", \"from\": 665, \"to\": 836, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 760, \"end\": 762, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RT_America\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.022948913856875e-36, \"text\": \"RT\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RT_America\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RT_America\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Figures\", \"from\": 665, \"to\": 672}, {\"ngram\": \"audience size\", \"from\": 683, \"to\": 696}, {\"ngram\": \"social media\", \"from\": 801, \"to\": 813}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the data to which we do have access suggests the existence of a sizable and growing following.\", \"from\": 837, \"to\": 935, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the data\", \"from\": 841, \"to\": 849}, {\"ngram\": \"the existence\", \"from\": 886, \"to\": 899}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To give a sense of scale, in 2018, RT Actualidad - the broadcaster's Spanish-language TV channel - had 18 million viewers, while its social media accounts had 25 million followers.\", \"from\": 937, \"to\": 1117, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a sense\", \"from\": 945, \"to\": 952}, {\"ngram\": \"scale\", \"from\": 956, \"to\": 961}, {\"ngram\": \"RT Actualidad\", \"from\": 972, \"to\": 985}, {\"ngram\": \"the broadcaster's Spanish-language TV channel\", \"from\": 988, \"to\": 1033}, {\"ngram\": \"18 million viewers\", \"from\": 1040, \"to\": 1058}, {\"ngram\": \"its social media accounts\", \"from\": 1066, \"to\": 1091}, {\"ngram\": \"25 million followers\", \"from\": 1096, \"to\": 1116}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Data from a year later puts weekly website visits to RT Arabic at 46.9 million, the outlet boasting five times more Facebook followers than either Al-Jazeera or Al-Arabiya.\", \"from\": 1118, \"to\": 1290, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1174, \"end\": 1180, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arab_world\", \"score\": 0.9999999996480256, \"rank\": 3.498664990982336e-10, \"text\": \"Arabic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arab_world\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arab_world\"}, {\"begin\": 1265, \"end\": 1275, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.396498309043421e-18, \"text\": \"Al-Jazeera\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera\"}, {\"begin\": 1279, \"end\": 1289, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Arabiya\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Al-Arabiya\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Arabiya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Arabiya\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Data\", \"from\": 1118, \"to\": 1122}, {\"ngram\": \"a year\", \"from\": 1128, \"to\": 1134}, {\"ngram\": \"weekly website visits\", \"from\": 1146, \"to\": 1167}, {\"ngram\": \"the outlet\", \"from\": 1198, \"to\": 1208}, {\"ngram\": \"five times more Facebook followers\", \"from\": 1218, \"to\": 1252}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2023 a new bureau was reportedly being set up in Algiers, showing that Russia saw an opportunity to carve out an even larger audience.\", \"from\": 1291, \"to\": 1428, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1365, \"end\": 1371, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2104398713757354e-15, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a new bureau\", \"from\": 1299, \"to\": 1311}, {\"ngram\": \"Algiers\", \"from\": 1343, \"to\": 1350}, {\"ngram\": \"an opportunity\", \"from\": 1376, \"to\": 1390}, {\"ngram\": \"an even larger audience\", \"from\": 1404, \"to\": 1427}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Similarly, the growth of RT en francais' Facebook page was largely due to new followers based in Francophone Africa.\", \"from\": 1430, \"to\": 1546, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1455, \"end\": 1457, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RT_America\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.022948913856875e-36, \"text\": \"RT\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RT_America\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RT_America\"}, {\"begin\": 1527, \"end\": 1545, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/African_French\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8140670648421693e-39, \"text\": \"Francophone Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/African_French\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/African_French\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the growth\", \"from\": 1441, \"to\": 1451}, {\"ngram\": \"new followers\", \"from\": 1504, \"to\": 1517}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After 2022, RT executives reportedly were reaching out to news outlets across the continent to establish strategic partnerships - notably in Mali, whose military government enjoys warm relations with the Kremlin.\", \"from\": 1547, \"to\": 1759, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1559, \"end\": 1561, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RT_America\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.022948913856875e-36, \"text\": \"RT\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RT_America\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RT_America\"}, {\"begin\": 1688, \"end\": 1692, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mali\", \"score\": 0.9980954813944262, \"rank\": 0.0019081527096772171, \"text\": \"Mali\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mali\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mali\"}, {\"begin\": 1751, \"end\": 1758, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_Russia\", \"score\": 0.99999999683223, \"rank\": 3.167900994365926e-09, \"text\": \"Kremlin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_Russia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"news outlets\", \"from\": 1605, \"to\": 1617}, {\"ngram\": \"the continent\", \"from\": 1625, \"to\": 1638}, {\"ngram\": \"strategic partnerships\", \"from\": 1652, \"to\": 1674}, {\"ngram\": \"whose military government\", \"from\": 1694, \"to\": 1719}, {\"ngram\": \"warm relations\", \"from\": 1727, \"to\": 1741}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Such growth is a relatively recent phenomenon, possibly resulting from RT's pivot from Russia-centric broadcasting to more local coverage due to a realization that was pithily summarized by Simonyan herself: \\\"Who is interested in watching news from Russia all day long?\\\"\", \"from\": 1761, \"to\": 2031, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1832, \"end\": 1834, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RT_America\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.022948913856875e-36, \"text\": \"RT\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RT_America\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RT_America\"}, {\"begin\": 2010, \"end\": 2016, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2104398713757354e-15, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Such growth\", \"from\": 1761, \"to\": 1772}, {\"ngram\": \"a relatively recent phenomenon\", \"from\": 1776, \"to\": 1806}, {\"ngram\": \"Russia-centric broadcasting\", \"from\": 1848, \"to\": 1875}, {\"ngram\": \"more local coverage\", \"from\": 1879, \"to\": 1898}, {\"ngram\": \"a realization\", \"from\": 1906, \"to\": 1919}, {\"ngram\": \"Simonyan\", \"from\": 1951, \"to\": 1959}, {\"ngram\": \"news\", \"from\": 2000, \"to\": 2004}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But what is RT actually saying to these relatively newly established audiences?\", \"from\": 2033, \"to\": 2112, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2045, \"end\": 2047, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RT_America\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.022948913856875e-36, \"text\": \"RT\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RT_America\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RT_America\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"these relatively newly established audiences\", \"from\": 2067, \"to\": 2111}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Consistent with the outlet's founding mission to provide an alternative perspective on world events, the West is unsurprisingly cast as an imperial hegemon, in full control of the international media sphere and intent on retaining its political grip on the world.\", \"from\": 2114, \"to\": 2377, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the outlet's founding mission\", \"from\": 2130, \"to\": 2159}, {\"ngram\": \"an alternative perspective\", \"from\": 2171, \"to\": 2197}, {\"ngram\": \"world events\", \"from\": 2201, \"to\": 2213}, {\"ngram\": \"the West\", \"from\": 2215, \"to\": 2223}, {\"ngram\": \"an imperial hegemon\", \"from\": 2250, \"to\": 2269}, {\"ngram\": \"full control\", \"from\": 2274, \"to\": 2286}, {\"ngram\": \"the international media sphere\", \"from\": 2290, \"to\": 2320}, {\"ngram\": \"its political grip\", \"from\": 2345, \"to\": 2363}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 2367, \"to\": 2376}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, the exact identity of this \\\"West\\\" shifts depending on location.\", \"from\": 2379, \"to\": 2451, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"However, the exact identity\", \"from\": 2379, \"to\": 2406}, {\"ngram\": \"this \\\"West\\\" shifts\", \"from\": 2410, \"to\": 2428}, {\"ngram\": \"location\", \"from\": 2442, \"to\": 2450}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Analysis from 2020 showed that \\\"EEUU\\\" (the Spanish acronym for USA) was the most-used keyword in RT Espanol's sub-headlines, while its Facebook page covered the U.S. more than any Latin American country.\", \"from\": 2452, \"to\": 2655, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2495, \"end\": 2502, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spanish_language\", \"score\": 0.9999999470710478, \"rank\": 5.1818721487599747e-08, \"text\": \"Spanish\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spanish_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spanish_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2515, \"end\": 2518, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.831889554470883e-19, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2549, \"end\": 2551, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RT_America\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.022948913856875e-36, \"text\": \"RT\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RT_America\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RT_America\"}, {\"begin\": 2632, \"end\": 2646, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Latin_America\", \"score\": 0.9999991852376888, \"rank\": 8.147626540453776e-07, \"text\": \"Latin American\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Latin_America\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Latin_America\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Analysis\", \"from\": 2452, \"to\": 2460}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"EEUU\", \"from\": 2483, \"to\": 2488}, {\"ngram\": \"the most-used keyword\", \"from\": 2524, \"to\": 2545}, {\"ngram\": \"headlines\", \"from\": 2566, \"to\": 2575}, {\"ngram\": \"its Facebook page\", \"from\": 2583, \"to\": 2600}, {\"ngram\": \"the U.S.\", \"from\": 2609, \"to\": 2617}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a demonstration of RT's concern with local context, anti-Westernism is equated with anti-Americanism when dealing with an audience likely already mistrustful of the U.S. due to its role in the continent's recent turbulent and murky political past.\", \"from\": 2657, \"to\": 2907, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2679, \"end\": 2681, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RT_America\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.022948913856875e-36, \"text\": \"RT\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RT_America\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RT_America\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a demonstration\", \"from\": 2660, \"to\": 2675}, {\"ngram\": \"local context\", \"from\": 2697, \"to\": 2710}, {\"ngram\": \"Westernism\", \"from\": 2717, \"to\": 2727}, {\"ngram\": \"Americanism\", \"from\": 2749, \"to\": 2760}, {\"ngram\": \"an audience\", \"from\": 2779, \"to\": 2790}, {\"ngram\": \"the U.S.\", \"from\": 2821, \"to\": 2829}, {\"ngram\": \"its role\", \"from\": 2837, \"to\": 2845}, {\"ngram\": \"the continent's recent turbulent and murky political past\", \"from\": 2849, \"to\": 2906}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Elsewhere, RT en francais' coverage of Francophone Africa frequently highlights ex-imperial power France as the primary evil.\", \"from\": 2909, \"to\": 3034, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2948, \"end\": 2966, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/African_French\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8140670648421693e-39, \"text\": \"Francophone Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/African_French\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/African_French\"}, {\"begin\": 3007, \"end\": 3013, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.9910889214461421, \"rank\": 0.00865655587403578, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"RT en francais' coverage\", \"from\": 2920, \"to\": 2944}, {\"ngram\": \"the primary evil\", \"from\": 3017, \"to\": 3033}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For instance, over half of the articles covering the Central African Republic between 2018 and 2023 mention France, referring to it as \\\"the old colonial power,\\\" lambasting it for its failed attempts to curb jihadism in the Sahel and casting its contemporary political class as desperate to continue its imperial subjugation of the Central African people.\", \"from\": 3035, \"to\": 3389, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3143, \"end\": 3149, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.9910889214461421, \"rank\": 0.00865655587403578, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\"}, {\"begin\": 3258, \"end\": 3263, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sahel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.957112475591318e-37, \"text\": \"Sahel\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sahel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sahel\"}, {\"begin\": 3366, \"end\": 3373, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Central_Europe\", \"score\": 0.7068433202819907, \"rank\": 0.41472594114835193, \"text\": \"Central\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Central_Europe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Central_Europe\"}, {\"begin\": 3374, \"end\": 3388, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Demographics_of_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"African people\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Demographics_of_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Demographics_of_Africa\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"instance\", \"from\": 3039, \"to\": 3047}, {\"ngram\": \"half\", \"from\": 3054, \"to\": 3058}, {\"ngram\": \"the articles\", \"from\": 3062, \"to\": 3074}, {\"ngram\": \"the Central African Republic\", \"from\": 3084, \"to\": 3112}, {\"ngram\": \"the old colonial power\", \"from\": 3171, \"to\": 3193}, {\"ngram\": \"its failed attempts\", \"from\": 3214, \"to\": 3233}, {\"ngram\": \"jihadism\", \"from\": 3242, \"to\": 3250}, {\"ngram\": \"its contemporary political class\", \"from\": 3276, \"to\": 3308}, {\"ngram\": \"its imperial subjugation\", \"from\": 3334, \"to\": 3358}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This local accommodation does not stop Russia from taking a central position in RT's international coverage.\", \"from\": 3391, \"to\": 3499, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3430, \"end\": 3436, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2104398713757354e-15, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 3471, \"end\": 3473, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RT_America\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.022948913856875e-36, \"text\": \"RT\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RT_America\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RT_America\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This local accommodation\", \"from\": 3391, \"to\": 3415}, {\"ngram\": \"a central position\", \"from\": 3449, \"to\": 3467}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Russia frequently appears as a co-sufferer at the hands of the omnipotent West.\", \"from\": 3500, \"to\": 3579, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3500, \"end\": 3506, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2104398713757354e-15, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a co\", \"from\": 3529, \"to\": 3533}, {\"ngram\": \"sufferer\", \"from\": 3534, \"to\": 3542}, {\"ngram\": \"the hands\", \"from\": 3546, \"to\": 3555}, {\"ngram\": \"the omnipotent West\", \"from\": 3559, \"to\": 3578}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the coverage of the Central African Republic, Russia is cast as the inheritor of the Soviet Union's anti-colonial legacy and repeated references are made to Russia's historic \\\"return\\\" to the continent, presumably in an effort to find identification with Central African readers with a recent national history of decolonization.\", \"from\": 3580, \"to\": 3910, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3629, \"end\": 3635, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2104398713757354e-15, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 3675, \"end\": 3680, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.625606160054961e-18, \"text\": \"Union\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 3740, \"end\": 3746, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2104398713757354e-15, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 3837, \"end\": 3844, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Central_Europe\", \"score\": 0.7068433202819907, \"rank\": 0.41472594114835193, \"text\": \"Central\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Central_Europe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Central_Europe\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the coverage\", \"from\": 3583, \"to\": 3595}, {\"ngram\": \"the Central African Republic\", \"from\": 3599, \"to\": 3627}, {\"ngram\": \"the inheritor\", \"from\": 3647, \"to\": 3660}, {\"ngram\": \"repeated references\", \"from\": 3708, \"to\": 3727}, {\"ngram\": \"the continent\", \"from\": 3770, \"to\": 3783}, {\"ngram\": \"an effort\", \"from\": 3799, \"to\": 3808}, {\"ngram\": \"identification\", \"from\": 3817, \"to\": 3831}, {\"ngram\": \"a recent national history\", \"from\": 3866, \"to\": 3891}, {\"ngram\": \"decolonization\", \"from\": 3895, \"to\": 3909}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Russia is also held up as an ideal partner on the world stage.\", \"from\": 3912, \"to\": 3974, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3912, \"end\": 3918, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2104398713757354e-15, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an ideal partner\", \"from\": 3938, \"to\": 3954}, {\"ngram\": \"the world stage\", \"from\": 3958, \"to\": 3973}]}, {\"sentence\": \"RT Arabic covers growing Russo-Saudi tourism links.\", \"from\": 3975, \"to\": 4026, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3978, \"end\": 3984, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arab_world\", \"score\": 0.9999999996480256, \"rank\": 3.498664990982336e-10, \"text\": \"Arabic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arab_world\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arab_world\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"growing Russo-Saudi tourism links\", \"from\": 3992, \"to\": 4025}]}, {\"sentence\": \"RT Espanol deals with apparent U.S. attempts to impede the tightening of Russo-Argentine relations and Bolivia's aspirations to join BRICS.\", \"from\": 4027, \"to\": 4166, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4027, \"end\": 4029, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RT_America\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.022948913856875e-36, \"text\": \"RT\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RT_America\",