reedom of speech and generally bolstered RT's constructed identity as \\\"just guys who tell the truth,\\\" as described by Simonyan when the outlet's social media pages were blocked on Tuesday.\", \"from\": 4333, \"to\": 4644, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4369, \"end\": 4385, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_Foreign_Office\", \"score\": 0.9919648469609672, \"rank\": 0.008066141493713123, \"text\": \"Foreign Ministry\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_Foreign_Office\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_Foreign_Office\"}, {\"begin\": 4399, \"end\": 4414, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maria_Zakharova\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Maria Zakharova\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maria_Zakharova\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maria_Zakharova\"}, {\"begin\": 4497, \"end\": 4499, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RT_America\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.022948913856875e-36, \"text\": \"RT\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RT_America\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RT_America\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"articles\", \"from\": 4347, \"to\": 4355}, {\"ngram\": \"the U.S.\", \"from\": 4429, \"to\": 4437}, {\"ngram\": \"freedom\", \"from\": 4455, \"to\": 4462}, {\"ngram\": \"speech\", \"from\": 4466, \"to\": 4472}, {\"ngram\": \"just guys\", \"from\": 4527, \"to\": 4536}, {\"ngram\": \"the truth\", \"from\": 4546, \"to\": 4555}, {\"ngram\": \"Simonyan\", \"from\": 4574, \"to\": 4582}, {\"ngram\": \"the outlet's social media pages\", \"from\": 4588, \"to\": 4619}, {\"ngram\": \"Tuesday\", \"from\": 4636, \"to\": 4643}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Of course, many countries broadcast news internationally.\", \"from\": 4646, \"to\": 4703, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"many countries\", \"from\": 4657, \"to\": 4671}, {\"ngram\": \"news\", \"from\": 4682, \"to\": 4686}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There is the BBC, CNN, Deutsche Welle, CGTN, France 24 \\u2026 the list goes on.\", \"from\": 4704, \"to\": 4778, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4717, \"end\": 4720, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_News\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 1.0616496841836462e-12, \"text\": \"BBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_News\"}, {\"begin\": 4722, \"end\": 4725, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNN\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.629685978152422e-20, \"text\": \"CNN\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNN\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNN\"}, {\"begin\": 4727, \"end\": 4741, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Deutsche_Welle\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2696901089678523e-63, \"text\": \"Deutsche Welle\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Deutsche_Welle\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Deutsche_Welle\"}, {\"begin\": 4749, \"end\": 4758, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_24\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"France 24\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_24\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_24\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"CGTN\", \"from\": 4743, \"to\": 4747}, {\"ngram\": \"the list\", \"from\": 4761, \"to\": 4769}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Arguably these help to mold public opinion abroad, or at least offer a somewhat favorable image of their sponsoring nation.\", \"from\": 4779, \"to\": 4902, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Arguably these help\", \"from\": 4779, \"to\": 4798}, {\"ngram\": \"public opinion\", \"from\": 4807, \"to\": 4821}, {\"ngram\": \"a somewhat favorable image\", \"from\": 4848, \"to\": 4874}, {\"ngram\": \"their sponsoring nation\", \"from\": 4878, \"to\": 4901}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is why it is difficult - except in cases of disinformation - to label Russia's media presence in the Global South as a problem in need of solutions.\", \"from\": 4904, \"to\": 5057, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4979, \"end\": 4985, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2104398713757354e-15, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"cases\", \"from\": 4944, \"to\": 4949}, {\"ngram\": \"disinformation\", \"from\": 4953, \"to\": 4967}, {\"ngram\": \"the Global South\", \"from\": 5006, \"to\": 5022}, {\"ngram\": \"a problem\", \"from\": 5026, \"to\": 5035}, {\"ngram\": \"need\", \"from\": 5039, \"to\": 5043}, {\"ngram\": \"solutions\", \"from\": 5047, \"to\": 5056}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To use this language merely supports the contention that the West is intent on maintaining hegemony.\", \"from\": 5058, \"to\": 5158, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this language\", \"from\": 5065, \"to\": 5078}, {\"ngram\": \"the contention\", \"from\": 5095, \"to\": 5109}, {\"ngram\": \"the West\", \"from\": 5115, \"to\": 5123}, {\"ngram\": \"hegemony\", \"from\": 5149, \"to\": 5157}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dr. Dani Madrid-Morales, a lecturer in global journalism at the University of Sheffield, suggested the most important thing was that the audiences being targeted have their own voice, that the West should \\\"let citizens make up their own minds\\\" and accept the fact that there might be a \\\"multiplicity of views\\\" resulting from the coverage which they consume.\", \"from\": 5160, \"to\": 5517, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Dr. Dani Madrid-Morales\", \"from\": 5160, \"to\": 5183}, {\"ngram\": \"a lecturer\", \"from\": 5185, \"to\": 5195}, {\"ngram\": \"global journalism\", \"from\": 5199, \"to\": 5216}, {\"ngram\": \"the University\", \"from\": 5220, \"to\": 5234}, {\"ngram\": \"Sheffield\", \"from\": 5238, \"to\": 5247}, {\"ngram\": \"the most important thing\", \"from\": 5259, \"to\": 5283}, {\"ngram\": \"the audiences\", \"from\": 5293, \"to\": 5306}, {\"ngram\": \"their own voice\", \"from\": 5327, \"to\": 5342}, {\"ngram\": \"the West\", \"from\": 5349, \"to\": 5357}, {\"ngram\": \"citizens\", \"from\": 5370, \"to\": 5378}, {\"ngram\": \"their own minds\", \"from\": 5387, \"to\": 5402}, {\"ngram\": \"the fact\", \"from\": 5415, \"to\": 5423}, {\"ngram\": \"a \\\"multiplicity\", \"from\": 5444, \"to\": 5459}, {\"ngram\": \"views\", \"from\": 5463, \"to\": 5468}, {\"ngram\": \"the coverage\", \"from\": 5485, \"to\": 5497}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Moreover, if audiences across the Global South find a Russian version of world events more compelling or attractive, bans and sanctions would do little to counter that.\", \"from\": 5518, \"to\": 5686, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5572, \"end\": 5579, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language\", \"score\": 0.9935948759219542, \"rank\": 0.006446412902383996, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"audiences\", \"from\": 5531, \"to\": 5540}, {\"ngram\": \"the Global South\", \"from\": 5548, \"to\": 5564}, {\"ngram\": \"world events\", \"from\": 5591, \"to\": 5603}, {\"ngram\": \"bans\", \"from\": 5635, \"to\": 5639}, {\"ngram\": \"sanctions\", \"from\": 5644, \"to\": 5653}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even when Latin American fact-checking organizations were asked in 2023 whether shutting down RT Actualidad was a potential solution to misinformation, the suggestion was shot down as they pointed out that this would merely bolster the network's claim that the West does not want audiences to hear the truth - something which only RT can be trusted to provide.\", \"from\": 5688, \"to\": 6048, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5698, \"end\": 5712, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Latin_America\", \"score\": 0.9999991852376888, \"rank\": 8.147626540453776e-07, \"text\": \"Latin American\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Latin_America\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Latin_America\"}, {\"begin\": 6019, \"end\": 6021, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RT_America\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.022948913856875e-36, \"text\": \"RT\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RT_America\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RT_America\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"RT Actualidad\", \"from\": 5782, \"to\": 5795}, {\"ngram\": \"a potential solution\", \"from\": 5800, \"to\": 5820}, {\"ngram\": \"misinformation\", \"from\": 5824, \"to\": 5838}, {\"ngram\": \"the suggestion\", \"from\": 5840, \"to\": 5854}, {\"ngram\": \"the network's claim\", \"from\": 5920, \"to\": 5939}, {\"ngram\": \"the West\", \"from\": 5945, \"to\": 5953}, {\"ngram\": \"audiences\", \"from\": 5968, \"to\": 5977}, {\"ngram\": \"the truth\", \"from\": 5986, \"to\": 5995}, {\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 5998, \"to\": 6007}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nonetheless, whilst attempting to muzzle RT's operations in the Global South is clearly not a viable nor logical step, that is not to say we should ignore the phenomenon entirely.\", \"from\": 6050, \"to\": 6229, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6091, \"end\": 6093, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RT_America\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.022948913856875e-36, \"text\": \"RT\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RT_America\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RT_America\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Global South\", \"from\": 6110, \"to\": 6126}, {\"ngram\": \"a viable nor logical step\", \"from\": 6142, \"to\": 6167}, {\"ngram\": \"the phenomenon\", \"from\": 6205, \"to\": 6219}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thirty-five countries abstained from the UN's 2022 resolution to condemn Russia's invasion of Ukraine and a reported 36 countries have expressed an interest in joining BRICS.\", \"from\": 6231, \"to\": 6405, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6272, \"end\": 6274, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Nations\", \"score\": 0.9999950838548892, \"rank\": 4.916169601639176e-06, \"text\": \"UN\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Nations\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Nations\"}, {\"begin\": 6304, \"end\": 6310, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2104398713757354e-15, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 6325, \"end\": 6332, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.9999999999809006, \"rank\": 1.938494784654493e-11, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}, {\"begin\": 6399, \"end\": 6404, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BRICS\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 1.5819162268016562e-12, \"text\": \"BRICS\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BRICS\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BRICS\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Thirty-five countries\", \"from\": 6231, \"to\": 6252}, {\"ngram\": \"a reported 36 countries\", \"from\": 6337, \"to\": 6360}, {\"ngram\": \"an interest\", \"from\": 6376, \"to\": 6387}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These are the signs of a shifting world order.\", \"from\": 6406, \"to\": 6452, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the signs\", \"from\": 6416, \"to\": 6425}, {\"ngram\": \"a shifting world order\", \"from\": 6429, \"to\": 6451}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If we are to understand how and why these changes are taking place, a good starting point would be to focus on how Russia is narrating world events to various countries across the Global South, and thus learn why it has been so successful in capturing their attention.\", \"from\": 6453, \"to\": 6721, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6568, \"end\": 6574, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2104398713757354e-15, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"these changes\", \"from\": 6489, \"to\": 6502}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 6514, \"to\": 6519}, {\"ngram\": \"a good starting point\", \"from\": 6521, \"to\": 6542}, {\"ngram\": \"world events\", \"from\": 6588, \"to\": 6600}, {\"ngram\": \"various countries\", \"from\": 6604, \"to\": 6621}, {\"ngram\": \"the Global South\", \"from\": 6629, \"to\": 6645}, {\"ngram\": \"their attention\", \"from\": 6705, \"to\": 6720}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The alternative is to remain arrogantly ignorant, a privilege which we cannot afford in these uncertain times.\", \"from\": 6723, \"to\": 6833, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The alternative\", \"from\": 6723, \"to\": 6738}, {\"ngram\": \"these uncertain times\", \"from\": 6811, \"to\": 6832}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A Message from The Moscow Times: Dear readers, We are facing unprecedented challenges.\", \"from\": 6835, \"to\": 6923, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6850, \"end\": 6866, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Moscow_Times\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"The Moscow Times\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Moscow_Times\", \"dbpedia\": \"